<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--SoccerRecord     01-03 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Soccer Record,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Czechs Play Indoor Soccer More Than Four Days Straight For Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twenty Czechs broke the world
record for indoor soccer last month, playing the game continuously
for 107 hours and 15 minutes, the official Czechoslovak news agency
CTK reported.
   Two teams began the endeavour in the West Bohemian town of
Holysov on Dec. 13 and ended with the new world record on Dec. 17,
CTK said in the dispatch Monday.
   According to the news agency, the previous record of 106 hours 10
minutes was held by English players. The Czechs new record is to be
recorded in the Guinness Book of World Records, CTK said.
</TEXT>
