<HEAD>13 Die in Mountain Bus Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus ran off a roadside cliff and
tumbled 165 feet down a ravine in the Andes mountains, killing 13
travelers and injuring 30, the government newspaper said Tuesday.
   The crash occurred late Monday night near Huambos, a mountain
hamlet 400 miles northeast of Lima, the La Cronica newspaper
reported.
   In preliminary reports, officials blamed the crash on poor
driving conditions caused by fog and wet roads, the newspaper said.
   The privately owned bus was en route from the highland town of
Chota to coastal Chiclayo, 120 miles west, La Cronica said.
   Two weeks ago, a bus crash in the Andes killed 21 passengers.
   Authorities said accidents in the mountains occur with greater
frequency from December to March, due to heavy seasonal rains that
worsen conditions on roads already poorly paved or made of dirt and
gravel.
