   The new year began on a sour note on Wall Street
today as the prospect of higher interest rates brought stock prices
lower.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was off 20.53 to 2,148.04
as of noon EST.
   Declining issues were ahead of advancers by a margin of about
8-to-5, with 491 stocks up, 852 down and 481 unchanged on the New
York Stock Exchange.
   Big Board volume totaled 59.83 million shares at midday.
   Analysts said interest rate worries and program selling combined
to bring the market down.
